Integrity Module

Multi-layered behavioral integrity enforcement for PostWins.

This module protects the system against:

Duplicate claims

Device abuse

Identity anomalies

Prompt injection attempts

High-severity behavioral violations

Replay attacks (idempotency)

It is not a moderation tool.

It is a system integrity firewall.

Core Principle

Integrity must be layered, stateful, and replay-safe.

A single check is fragile.
A layered audit is resilient.

This module enforces:

Behavioral controls

Identity pattern analysis

Cooldown enforcement

Violation escalation

Permanent blacklist

Idempotency persistence

Responsibilities

This service owns:

Full integrity audit (Section F & M policies)

Device-to-beneficiary anomaly detection

Cooldown-based rate defense

Adversarial input detection

Violation counting

Permanent blacklist enforcement

File-backed idempotency storage

It does NOT:

Mutate domain state

Approve/reject cases

Perform ledger writes

Enforce business lifecycle rules

It returns flags.

The caller decides enforcement.

Integrity Layers

1. Blacklist Enforcement (Section M.5)

If a device is blacklisted:

Immediate HIGH severity flag.

No further processing.

Blacklist is persisted to disk and survives restarts.

This is a permanent ban list.

2. Cooldown Check (Section M.4)

Devices may not send messages within 30 seconds.

If violated:

LOW severity flag.

Prevents automated flooding without blocking legitimate retry.

3. Duplicate Detection (Section F)

Raw message is normalized and hashed in-memory.

Duplicate submission returns:

HIGH severity DUPLICATE_CLAIM

Protects against replay abuse.

Current behavior:
In-memory only (resets on restart).

4. Ghost Beneficiary Detection (Section M.1)

A single device linking to more than 3 beneficiaries triggers:

HIGH severity IDENTITY_MISMATCH

This prevents:

Device farming

Identity cycling

Cross-claim abuse

Registry is persisted to disk.

5. Adversarial Input Shield (Section M.2)

Detects patterns like:

“ignore previous instructions”

“system override”

<script>

Returns HIGH severity SUSPICIOUS_TONE.

This protects:

AI prompt boundaries

Execution instructions

Embedded injection attempts

Pattern list is extensible.

6. Violation Escalation

Every HIGH severity flag increments violation counter.

If count >= 5:

Device is permanently blacklisted.

Blacklist persisted immediately.

Escalation is automatic.

No human approval required.

Idempotency Persistence

This module also acts as the backing store for idempotency middleware.

Stored in:

data/idempotency.json

Structure:

{
  keys: {
    "idempotency-key": {
      requestHash,
      response,
      recordedAt
    }
  }
}

Capabilities:

get(key)

save(key, requestHash, response)

Allows:

Safe retries

Crash recovery

Horizontal restart resilience

Replay prevention

If persistence fails:

System degrades to best-effort.

Integrity must never crash request pipeline.

Persistence Model

File-backed JSON storage:

device_registry.json

blacklist.json

data/idempotency.json

Using:

process.cwd() to ensure compatibility across dev and dist builds.

Why file-based?

Because this module operates as:

Edge-layer guard.

It must function:

Even if DB unavailable

Before Prisma boots

In minimal infrastructure mode

Important Constraints

This module is not horizontally scalable as-is.

State lives in:

Memory

Local disk

In multi-instance deployments:

Replace file persistence with:

Redis

Distributed cache

Durable KV store

Database-backed integrity store

Without that, integrity becomes node-local.

Failure Philosophy

If persistence fails:

Do not throw

Do not block UX

Log error

Continue best-effort enforcement

Integrity must degrade safely.

Blocking legitimate traffic due to file I/O error is worse than soft enforcement.

Security Boundaries

This module must never:

Trust client-provided deviceId blindly (validate upstream)

Expose blacklist content

Expose registry structure

Expose violation counts

Leak persistence paths

It is defensive infrastructure.

Not public API.

Configuration Constants
COOLDOWN_MS = 30000
MAX_VIOLATIONS = 5

These are policy thresholds.

If changed:

Re-evaluate:

False positive rate

Abuse tolerance

Operational load

Performance Characteristics

Duplicate check: O(1) in-memory

Cooldown: O(1)

Ghost detection: O(n) per device (small n)

Idempotency lookup: O(1) JSON object

File write: synchronous (blocking)

For high throughput:

Move idempotency to async storage

Replace fs.writeFileSync with append or transactional write

Introduce distributed locking

Attack Surfaces Considered

Replay spam

Rapid message flooding

Multi-beneficiary abuse

Prompt injection attempts

Token replay across restarts

Idempotency key collision

What This Module Is Not

It is not:

Fraud detection ML

Financial risk engine

Ledger reconciliation

Access control

Authorization layer

It is behavioral integrity guardrail.

Determinism

Given same:

deviceId

message

beneficiary mapping

violation history

This module must produce same flags.

No randomness.
No external state.
No hidden mutation outside defined maps.

Production Hardening Recommendations

For enterprise scale:

Move blacklist to DB or Redis.

Move idempotency to Redis with TTL.

Introduce atomic compare-and-set for idempotency.

Add distributed rate limiting.

Introduce structured violation logs.

Add observability counters.

File storage is acceptable for early stage or controlled environment.

Not for distributed production clusters.

Mental Model

This module is the immune system.

It does not make decisions.
It raises inflammation signals.

If too weak:
Abuse spreads.

If too aggressive:
Healthy traffic suffers.

Balance is governance.

Ready for the next domain boundary.

